description:
&lt;p&gt;A number of exciting opportunities have arisen for District Nurse Community Nursing Sister / Charge Nurse roles in the Derby City area. This is an ideal opportunity for experienced band five community staff nurses who wish to develop their leadership and management skills in a supportive environment to manage a caseload. The successful applicants would require a minimum of two years community nursing experience, a thorough knowledge of caseload management with a high standard of community nursing knowledge and clinical skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This will be considered for a 12 month Secondment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are 3 posts available all based at Village Medical Centre working with the following teams:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mickleover DN Team 37.5 hours/per week from September 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Macklin DN Team 37.5 hours/per week from December 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Friargate DN Team - 30 hours/per week...please note the vacancy in this team is for 9 months only from Jan 2021&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sally Hobbs&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Integrated Community Team Lead&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;s.hobbs@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;07721 879923&lt;/p&gt;
